<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idec108708-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s71102"><num value="71102">§ 71102.</num><heading> Requests for information</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Administrator shall issue requests for information on—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec108709-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s71102/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a low-cost space mission with the purpose of rendezvousing with, attaching a tracking device,<ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002016">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002016"><num>1</num> So in original. The comma probably should be preceded by “to”.</note> and characterizing the Apophis asteroid; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec10870a-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s71102/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> a medium-sized space mission with the purpose of detecting near-Earth objects equal to or greater than 140 meters in diameter.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idec10870b-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/314/s3">Pub. L. 111–314, § 3</ref>, <date date="2010-12-18">Dec. 18, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3439">124 Stat. 3439</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
